{
  "chapter": {
    "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.10",
    "translationId": "rsv",
    "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
    "chapterNumber": 10,
    "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10",
    "summary": "Source text for Ecclesiastes 10 in Revised Standard Version."
  },
  "verses": [
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.10.1",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 1,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:1",
      "text": "Dead flies make the perfumer's ointment give off an evil odor; so a little folly outweighs wisdom and honor.",
      "paragraphStart": true
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.10.2",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 2,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:2",
      "text": "A wise man's heart inclines him toward the right, but a fool's heart toward the left.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.10.3",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 3,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:3",
      "text": "Even when the fool walks on the road, he lacks sense, and he says to every one that he is a fool.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.10.4",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 4,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:4",
      "text": "If the anger of the ruler rises against you, do not leave your place, for deference will make amends for great offenses.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.10.5",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 5,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:5",
      "text": "There is an evil which I have seen under the sun, as it were an error proceeding from the ruler:",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.10.6",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 6,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:6",
      "text": "folly is set in many high places, and the rich sit in a low place.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.10.7",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 7,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:7",
      "text": "I have seen slaves on horses, and princes walking on foot like slaves.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.10.8",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 8,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:8",
      "text": "He who digs a pit will fall into it; and a serpent will bite him who breaks through a wall.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.10.9",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 9,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:9",
      "text": "He who quarries stones is hurt by them; and he who splits logs is endangered by them.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.10.10",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 10,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:10",
      "text": "If the iron is blunt, and one does not whet the edge, he must put forth more strength; but wisdom helps one to succeed.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.10.11",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 11,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:11",
      "text": "If the serpent bites before it is charmed, there is no advantage in a charmer.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.10.12",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 12,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:12",
      "text": "The words of a wise man's mouth win him favor, but the lips of a fool consume him.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.10.13",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 13,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:13",
      "text": "The beginning of the words of his mouth is foolishness, and the end of his talk is wicked madness.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.10.14",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 14,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:14",
      "text": "A fool multiplies words, though no man knows what is to be, and who can tell him what will be after him?",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.10.15",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 15,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:15",
      "text": "The toil of a fool wearies him, so that he does not know the way to the city.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.10.16",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 16,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:16",
      "text": "Woe to you, O land, when your king is a child, and your princes feast in the morning!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.10.17",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 17,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:17",
      "text": "Happy are you, O land, when your king is the son of free men, and your princes feast at the proper time, for strength, and not for drunkenness!",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.10.18",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 18,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:18",
      "text": "Through sloth the roof sinks in, and through indolence the house leaks.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.10.19",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 19,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:19",
      "text": "Bread is made for laughter, and wine gladdens life, and money answers everything.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    },
    {
      "id": "rsv:ecclesiastes.10.20",
      "translationId": "rsv",
      "bookSlug": "ecclesiastes",
      "chapterNumber": 10,
      "verseNumber": 20,
      "referenceLabel": "Ecclesiastes 10:20",
      "text": "Even in your thought, do not curse the king, nor in your bedchamber curse the rich; for a bird of the air will carry your voice, or some winged creature tell the matter.",
      "paragraphStart": false
    }
  ]
}
